@CCNY

Yikes. Crosswords as long as I can remember (thanks, Grandma!), and NYT Sundays for probably 25 years. Mostly in books and in the Sunday paper for a few years. (I'm on Omnibus 11 and will return to pre-Shortz after I've exhausted all other options. 😉)

It just makes more sense to me to focus on the list of clues and fill when applicable than to bounce back and forth between the grid and the list. I kept the same MO when I switched to the app in and started solving daily (plus several years of Archives) in 2018.

Now you have me thinking about whether I miss some of the fun by not solving the grid as a grid, if that makes sense. I'll give the NE to SE maze a try for a week and report back!

