But I don't typically see it as a brag when people do. I think it's just the way they share their excitement or improvement or as how they analyze their own performance.

@Jon 

Uhh, the game does that: keep track of times, that is. The Statistics are there; whether or not you look at / reference / share them is another matter. 

As for commenters discussing their stats (times, streaks, or whatever else), why assume they do it to brag?? Everyone comes to this community with their own interests, and speed-solving certainly is one of them. Personally I find those conversations rather dry -- so I just skip over them. No harm, no foul: no affront taken!
